INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10749165142319', '[April 18, 2025] The Equine Distal Limb: An Atlas of Clinical Anatomy and Comparative Imaging 2nd Edition', 59, 'Your Definitive Atlas of Equine Distal Limb Anatomy This book is a reference atlas of the clinical anatomy of the foot, pastern, and fetlock, correlated with images obtained by radiography, diagnostic ultrasonography, and magnetic resonance imaging. This new edition replaces most of the ultrasound, radiographic, and MRI images with updated, extraordinarily high-quality versions. The atlas is essential for anybody involved in detailed anatomical study, complex lameness evaluation, or advanced imaging techniques. Key Features Extensive Visuals : Every part opens with a superb anatomical drawing by the author. Each double-page spread deals with a single dissection viewed by means of color photographs , labeled B&amp;W equivalents, plus x-rays, ultrasound, and MRI scans as required. Updated Images : This new edition replaces ultrasound images and most of the radiographic and MRI images with new, updated versions and adds brand new images of extraordinarily high quality. Detailed Evaluation : The multiple views of each area of the distal limb provide an extremely detailed evaluation. Clinical Relevance : Diagnosis and management of distal limb lameness require a precise knowledge of the functional anatomy and biomechanics of the equine distal joints, ligaments, and tendons, presented in the last chapter. Maximum Clarity : The atlas is designed for maximum clarity using a generous page size. Expert Authorship : The book is compiled by a leading equine musculoskeletal system anatomist and one of the foremost equine diagnostic ultrasonographers, making it an invaluable reference text.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/810rUGw6vfL._SL1500__1.jpg?v=1758352963', '', '2025 Books', '["2025-books","animals"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10749107306799', '[July 9, 2025] Harkness and Wagner''s Biology and Medicine of Rabbits and Rodents 6th Edition', 49, 'Your Practical Guide to Small Mammal Health and Husbandry, 6th Edition This book provides a thorough update to the classic reference on small mammal health and husbandry, now with full-color clinical photographs throughout. This comprehensive, practical guide is equally useful in research, companion animal practice, or food animal settings, and is an essential reference for veterinary professionals and students. Key Features Comprehensive Coverage : It provides a comprehensive, practical guide to caring for rabbits, guinea pigs, hamsters, gerbils, mice, rats , and chinchillas . New Topics : New topics for the Sixth Edition include environmental monitoring for rodent health assessments, behavioral management considerations for optimizing animal health, enhanced pain assessment approaches, as well as considerations for creating a welfare-friendly small mammal practice . Clinical Procedures : The book covers a wide range of clinical procedures, including hematology, clinical chemistry, urinalysis, surgery, post-operative care, dentistry, ophthalmology , and imaging . Genetic Engineering : It covers new techniques for creating and modifying genetically engineered rodents , reflecting the latest advances in research. Updated Information : The Sixth Edition also updates common therapeutics, analgesics, anesthetics , and blood collection methodology , disease biology, husbandry, diagnostic modalities, and references. Broad Audience : An essential reference for veterinary professionals dealing with small mammal species in research or practice settings, as well as veterinary students interested in small animals, comparative medicine, or laboratory animal medicine.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/81wFWtyfpcL._SL1500.jpg?v=175832